    "body": "A bug was found where a generated like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nval df = Seq((-127, -3E+200 * 1e200), (-126, 123.1)).toDF(\"a\", \"b\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that `-3E+200 * 1e200` becomes `-Infinity`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n+----+---------+\r\n|   a|        b|\r\n+----+---------+\r\n|-127|-Infinity|\r\n|-126|    123.1|\r\n+----+---------+\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen grouped using max:\r\n```\r\ndf.groupBy(\"a\").agg(max(\"b\")).collect\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe GPU produces `Double.MaxValue` for the grouping key `-127`, instead of `-Infinity` like the CPU does:\r\n\r\nGPU:\r\n```\r\nres6: Array[org.apache.spark.sql.Row] = Array([-126,123.1], [-127,-1.7976931348623157E308])\r\n```\r\n\r\nCPU:\r\n```\r\nres8: Array[org.apache.spark.sql.Row] = Array([-126,123.1], [-127,-Infinity])\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that this is an issue if `spark.rapids.sql.hasNans=false`, so it is related to this effort: https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/issues/5320\r\n\r\nThis is a behavior in cuDF, documented here: https://github.com/rapidsai/cudf/issues/11352, but our testing never caught this. It seems we should have some tests where we add some more targeted corner cases to cover this.\r\n",
